<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="157" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,498,1118,1144]" box="[151,498,1118,1144]" pageId="6" pageNumber="157">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,498,1118,1144]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="6" pageNumber="157" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,498,1118,1144]" pageId="6" pageNumber="157">
Genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Selys, 1853" authorityName="Selys" authorityYear="1853" box="[238,498,1118,1144]" class="Insecta" family="Euphaeidae" genus="Bayadera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="6" pageNumber="157" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[238,354,1118,1144]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="157">Bayadera</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Selys" box="[360,498,1118,1144]" pageId="6" pageNumber="157" refString="Selys Longchamps, E. de (1853) Synopsis des Calopterygines. Bulletins de l'Academie Royale des sciences, des lettres et des beaux-arts de Belgique, 20, 1 - 73." type="journal article" year="1853">Selys, 1853</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,1188,1646]" pageId="6" pageNumber="157">
The genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Selys" authorityYear="1853" box="[284,393,1188,1213]" class="Insecta" family="Euphaeidae" genus="Bayadera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="6" pageNumber="157" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[284,393,1188,1213]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="157">Bayadera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
consists of medium-sized stream-dwelling damselflies. They are characterized by wings petiolated to the level of the first antenodal crossvein and IR3 merging close to its base with the radius (
<bibRefCitation author="Davies" pageId="6" pageNumber="157" refString="Davies, D. A. L. &amp; Yang, B. (1996) New species of Bayadera Selys and Schmidtiphaea Asahina from China (Odonata, Euphaeidae). Tijdschrift voor Entomologie, 139, 145 - 155." type="journal article" year="1996">Davies &amp; Yang 1996</bibRefCitation>
). This genus is widely distributed across 
<collectingCountry box="[758,818,1260,1285]" name="India" pageId="6" pageNumber="157">India</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[832,902,1260,1285]" name="Nepal" pageId="6" pageNumber="157">Nepal</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[916,983,1262,1285]" name="Japan" pageId="6" pageNumber="157">Japan</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[996,1081,1260,1285]" name="Taiwan" pageId="6" pageNumber="157">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
, southern 
<collectingCountry box="[1200,1267,1260,1285]" name="China" pageId="6" pageNumber="157">China</collectingCountry>
and Southeast Asia. A total of 17 species, presently ranked as valid, have been described (
<bibRefCitation author="Hamalainen" box="[1016,1221,1297,1322]" pageId="6" pageNumber="157" refString="Hamalainen, M. (2016) Calopterygoidea of the world: A synonymic list of extant damselfly species of the superfamily Calopterygoidea (sensu lato) (Odonata: Zygoptera). 1 st Edition. 1 January 2016. Privately published online, Espoo, Finland. Available from: http: // www. caloptera. com / World-Calopterygoidea-List. pdf (accessed 12 July 2017)" type="journal article" year="2016">Hämäläinen 2016</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Schorr" pageId="6" pageNumber="157" refString="Schorr, M. &amp; Paulson, D. (2017) World Odonata List. Available from: http: // www. pugetsound. edu / academics / academicresources / slater-museum / biodiversity-resources / dragonflies / world-odonata-list 2 / (accessed 26 November 2017)" type="journal article" year="2017">Schorr &amp; Paulson 2017</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Davies" box="[235,503,1332,1358]" pageId="6" pageNumber="157" refString="Davies, D. A. L. &amp; Yang, B. (1996) New species of Bayadera Selys and Schmidtiphaea Asahina from China (Odonata, Euphaeidae). Tijdschrift voor Entomologie, 139, 145 - 155." type="journal article" year="1996">Davies &amp; Yang (1996)</bibRefCitation>
described several species, including three new ones, from southern 
<collectingCountry box="[1317,1384,1332,1357]" name="China" pageId="6" pageNumber="157">China</collectingCountry>
and provided an identification key. Later, 
<bibRefCitation author="Hamalainen" box="[601,824,1369,1394]" pageId="6" pageNumber="157" refString="Hamalainen, M. (2004) Caloptera damselflies from Fujian (China), with description of a new species and taxonomic notes (Zygoptera: Calopterygoidea). Odonatologica, 33, 371 - 398." type="journal article" year="2004">Hämäläinen (2004)</bibRefCitation>
showed the variation of wing pattern of 
<taxonomicName authority="Ris, 1912" authorityName=": Ris" authorityYear="1912" class="Insecta" family="Euphaeidae" genus="Bayadera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="6" pageNumber="157" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="melanopteryx">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="157">Bayadera melanopteryx</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Ris" box="[314,425,1405,1430]" pageId="6" pageNumber="157" refString="Ris, F. (1912) Neue Libellen von Formosa, Sudchina, Tonkin und den Philippinen. Supplementa Entomologica, 1, 44 - 85, pls. III-V excl." type="journal article" year="1912">
Ris, 
<quantity box="[369,425,1405,1429]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.85648" pageId="6" pageNumber="157" unit="in" value="1912.0">1912</quantity>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<collectingCountry box="[468,535,1405,1430]" name="China" pageId="6" pageNumber="157">China</collectingCountry>
and elevated three subspecies of 
<taxonomicName authority="Fraser, 1928" authorityName="Fraser" authorityYear="1928" box="[931,1244,1405,1430]" class="Insecta" family="Euphaeidae" genus="Bayadera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="6" pageNumber="157" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevicauda">
<emphasis box="[931,1090,1405,1430]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="157">B. brevicauda</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Fraser" box="[1101,1244,1405,1429]" pageId="6" pageNumber="157" refString="Fraser, F. C. (1928) Indian dragonflies, Part XXXI. Journal of the Bombay Natural History Society, 33, 47 - 59, pls. I - III excl." type="journal article" year="1928">Fraser, 1928</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
to distinct good species: 
<taxonomicName authority="Fraser, 1928" authorityName="Fraser" authorityYear="1928" box="[250,566,1441,1466]" class="Insecta" family="Euphaeidae" genus="Bayadera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="6" pageNumber="157" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevicauda">
<emphasis box="[250,410,1441,1466]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="157">B. brevicauda</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Fraser" box="[420,566,1441,1465]" pageId="6" pageNumber="157" refString="Fraser, F. C. (1928) Indian dragonflies, Part XXXI. Journal of the Bombay Natural History Society, 33, 47 - 59, pls. I - III excl." type="journal article" year="1928">Fraser, 1928</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Asahina, 1964" authorityName="Asahina" authorityYear="1964" box="[580,925,1441,1466]" class="Insecta" family="Euphaeidae" genus="Bayadera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="6" pageNumber="157" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ishigakiana">
<emphasis box="[580,746,1441,1466]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="157">B. ishigakiana</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Asahina" box="[756,925,1441,1466]" pageId="6" pageNumber="157" refString="Asahina, S. (1964) Records of Thailand Odonata taken by Prof. Iwata, Dr. K. Yoshikawa and Mr. H. Ikoma. Nature and Life in Southeast Asia, 3, 113 - 115." type="journal article" year="1964">Asahina, 1964</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="Asahina, 1973" authorityName="Asahina" authorityYear="1973" box="[990,1348,1441,1466]" class="Insecta" family="Euphaeidae" genus="Bayadera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="6" pageNumber="157" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="continentalis">
<emphasis box="[990,1170,1441,1466]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="157">B. continentalis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Asahina" box="[1180,1348,1441,1466]" pageId="6" pageNumber="157" refString="Asahina, S. (1973) Notes on the Chinese Odonata, IV. D. G. Graham collection from Szechuan and T. H. Cheng collection from Fukien. Kontyu, 41, 446 - 460." type="journal article" year="1973">Asahina, 1973</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, with a discussion on their morphological characteristics. Recently two more species were described: 
<taxonomicName authority="Hamalainen, 2013" authorityName="Hamalainen" authorityYear="2013" class="Insecta" family="Euphaeidae" genus="Bayadera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="6" pageNumber="157" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kinnara">
<emphasis box="[1230,1436,1477,1502]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="157">Bayadera kinnara</emphasis>
Hämäläinen, 2013
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[431,540,1514,1538]" name="Myanmar" pageId="6" pageNumber="157">Myanmar</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingCountry box="[556,635,1513,1537]" name="Myanmar" pageId="6" pageNumber="157">Burma</collectingCountry>
) and 
<taxonomicName authority="Hamalainen &amp; Kompier, 2015" authorityName=": Hamalainen &amp; Kompier" authorityYear="2015" box="[701,1165,1513,1538]" class="Insecta" family="Euphaeidae" genus="Bayadera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="6" pageNumber="157" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hatvan">
<emphasis box="[701,811,1513,1538]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="157">B. hatvan</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Hamalainen" box="[820,1165,1513,1538]" pageId="6" pageNumber="157" refString="Hamalainen, M. &amp; Kompier, T. (2015) Bayadera hatvan sp. nov. from northern Vietnam (Odonata: Euphaeidae). Tombo - Acta Odonatologica Japonica, 57, 15 - 19." type="journal article" year="2015">Hämäläinen &amp; Kompier, 2015</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
from northern 
<collectingCountry box="[1341,1436,1513,1538]" name="Vietnam" pageId="6" pageNumber="157">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
(Hämäläinen 2013, 
<bibRefCitation author="Hamalainen" box="[381,729,1549,1574]" pageId="6" pageNumber="157" refString="Hamalainen, M. &amp; Kompier, T. (2015) Bayadera hatvan sp. nov. from northern Vietnam (Odonata: Euphaeidae). Tombo - Acta Odonatologica Japonica, 57, 15 - 19." type="journal article" year="2015">Hämäläinen &amp; Kompier 2015</bibRefCitation>
, respectively). From 
<collectingCountry box="[980,1077,1549,1574]" name="Vietnam" pageId="6" pageNumber="157">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
, seven species have now been confirmed, of which three are recorded for the first time in this paper. Female of 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Davies &amp; Yang" authorityYear="1996" box="[1059,1256,1585,1610]" class="Insecta" family="Euphaeidae" genus="Bayadera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="6" pageNumber="157" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="serrata">
<emphasis box="[1059,1256,1585,1610]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="157">Bayadera serrata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is described for the first time.
</paragraph>
